, but the two differ morphologically, and karyotypic rear rangement resulted in several pericentric inversions. Molecular data support close relationships with M. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuroda" authorityYear="1940" box="[1087,1185,2857,2890]" class="Mammalia" family="Talpidae" genus="Mogera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="21" pageNumber="616" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tokudae">tokudae</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
